		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../atem.png" alt="ATEM 2006 SI"></a><br><code>atem2006s/paper02</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">ATEM 2006 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Ontological Approach for the Semantic Recovery of Traceability Links between Software Artefacts</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/YonggangZhang.html">Yonggang Zhang</a>, <a href="../profile/RenéWitte.html">René Witte</a>, <a href="../profile/JuergenRilling.html">Juergen Rilling</a>, <a href="../profile/VolkerHaarslev.html">Volker Haarslev</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1049/iet-sen:20070062">10.1049/iet-sen:20070062</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-540-69489-2_8"><em>A Unified Ontology-Based Process Model for Software Maintenance and Comprehension (ATEM 2006)</em></a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5g.html"><span class="tagM">T5G: Traceability</span></a><ul><li> The paper’s central goal is to recover (re-establish) traceability links between documentation and source code at fine granularity.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagL">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> It relies on formal ontological representations and ontology reasoning to infer explicit and implicit relations among artefacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2b.html"><span class="tagL">T2B: Evolution</span></a><ul><li> The motivation and application context are software comprehension and maintenance, where missing links hamper evolution activities.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports on applying and evaluating the approach (including an application example) to assess the recovered links and reasoning benefits.
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
	</body>
